# Privacy & GDPR (JOBBIE)

See [docs/GDPR-PRIVACY.md](../../docs/GDPR-PRIVACY.md) for the full runbook.

## CV & employer database

- Employers see a CV only when `cvs.visible_to_employers = true`, candidate `profiles.public_show_in_company_search !== false`, and individual role.
- Contact fields (`email`, `phone`, `linkedin_url`, full address, `birth_date`) on employer detail only when `show_contact_details` **or** `cv_contact_unlocks` row exists for `(company_id, cv_id)`.
- Never return `gender`, `has_disability`, or birth date to employer list/detail DTOs.
- Redact `references[].email` / `phone` under the same contact rule.
- `profiles.public_allow_platform_contact === false` blocks platform chat from CV database flows.

## Addresses & public catalog

- Jobs: null `location_address` when `show_exact_address` is false (mapper + `job_offers_public` view).
- Company ads: null `street_address` when `show_exact_address` is false (mapper + `company_ads_public` view).
- Public profile: respect `public_show_address`, `public_show_phone`, `public_show_account_email`, `public_profile_enabled`.

## Email

- Job alert digests: transactional — use `job_email_alerts` notification category; include per-alert pause link and category unsubscribe link.
- Marketing / digest: require `marketing_processing_consent` (and channel prefs); include unsubscribe token.
- Record changes in `consent_events` via `ConsentEventsService` (service_role insert).

## Account rights

- Delete: `POST /api/profiles/me/delete` only — scrub profile, hide CVs, deactivate alerts, ban auth user.
- Export: `GET /api/profiles/me/export` — ZIP with `data.json`; add new personal data fields to `DataExportService` when extending schema.
- Public token routes: `@Public()` on `public/notification-preferences` and `public/job-alerts`.

## Database

- `cv_personal_info`: sensitive columns revoked from `authenticated`/`anon`; contact via Nest unlock logic only.
- New PII tables: default deny RLS; no broad grants on `consent_events` inserts from clients.
